  "prompt": "I have forgotten ssc cgl password, what should I do now?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your SSC CGL (Staff Selection Commission Combined Graduate Level) exam password, you can follow these steps to recover it:\n\n1. **Visit the SSC Official Website**: Go to the official SSC website, which is [ssc.nic.in](https://ssc.nic.in/).\n\n2. **Find the Login Section**: On the homepage, look for the \"Login\" button or link. This is typically found in the candidate's section.\n\n3. **Forgot Password Link**: Below the login fields, you should see a \"Forgot Password\" link. Click on this link.\n\n4. **Enter Required Details**: You will be prompted to enter certain details to verify your identity. Commonly required details include:\n    - Your username\n    - Registered email ID\n    - Registered mobile number\n    - Other personal details\n\n5. **Receive Recovery Options**: Depending on the information you provide, you may receive a password reset link or a temporary password via email or SMS.\n\n6. **Follow the Instructions**: Use the link or temporary password to log in. Then, set a new password.\n\nIf you are having trouble with the above steps or if you do not receive the password reset options, you might need to contact the SSC support team for further assistance. Look for the contact details on the SSC website for the regional office responsible for your application.\n\nAdditionally, ensure to check your spam/junk folder if you do not see the recovery email in your inbox.",
